adenocarcinoma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Diffuse wall thickening","Distinct tumour margins","Polypoid growth pattern","Superficial mucosal erosion","Well-formed glandular structures"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDiffuse gastric adenocarcinoma is characterised by \u003Cstrong\u003Ediffuse wall thickening\u003C/strong\u003E due to infiltration of poorly cohesive single cells or small clusters throughout the gastric wall. This pattern leads to a leather bottle appearance known as linitis plastica (Image).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe tumour does not form a discrete mass with a \u003Cstrong\u003Epolypoid growth pattern\u003C/strong\u003E or show \u003Cstrong\u003Ewell-formed glandular structures\u003C/strong\u003E. Unlike intestinal-type adenocarcinoma, diffuse-type does not have \u003Cstrong\u003Edistinct tumour margins\u003C/strong\u003E and typically infiltrates widely through the stomach wall rather than causing \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperficial mucosal erosion\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis diffuse infiltrative pattern results in a worse prognosis compared to intestinal-type adenocarcinoma, as it is often diagnosed at a later stage and is more difficult to resect completely.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Diffuse gastric adenocarcinoma is characterised by poorly cohesive cells that infiltrate the gastric wall causing thickening without forming distinct glandular structures.","The Lauren classification divides gastric adenocarcinoma into intestinal and diffuse types, which have different morphological and prognostic features."],"references":["Ajani JA, Lee J, Sano T, Janjigian YY, Fan D, Song S. Gastric adenocarcinoma. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2017 Jun 1;3:17036. doi: 10.1038/nrdp.2017.36. PMID: 28569272","Smyth EC, Nilsson M, Grabsch HI, van Grieken NC, Lordick F. Gastric cancer. Lancet. 2020 Aug 29;396(10251):635-648. doi: 10.1016/S0140-6736(20)31288-5. PMID: 32861308","Mukkamalla SKR, Recio-Boiles A, Babiker HM. Gastric Cancer. [Updated 2023 Jul 4]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK459142/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Turner ES, Turner JR. Expanding the Lauren classification: a new gastric cancer subtype? Gastroenterology. 2013 Sep;145(3):505-8. doi: 10.1053/j.gastro.2013.07.019. Epub 2013 Jul 25. PMID: 23891604."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51416"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15176"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21259"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21259","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21259"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/rxxo0Cnb5tdljds52fAhFSwkqenWvS.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/rxxo0Cnb5tdljds52fAhFSwkqenWvS.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":385}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51416","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51416"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-28T10:29:27+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-28T10:29:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7867"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65967"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","link